      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): detect stale persisted registry when configured source plugins are missing (fixes #96046)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96046.\n\nWhen a persisted plugin registry already exists, Gateway validation can reuse it without noticing that a configured plugin has since been added under the auto-discovered global extensions root (`$OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/extensions`). That leaves `plugins.slots.memory` validating against stale `knownIds` and reporting `plugin not found` even though `plugins list` and `plugins registry --refresh` can see the same plugin.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change treats the persisted registry as stale when all of these are true:\n- the user config references the plugin through `plugins.entries`, `plugins.allow`, or `plugins.slots`\n- the persisted index does not contain that plugin id\n- a matching `openclaw.plugin.json` exists under the global extensions root\n\nIn that case, registry loading falls back to derived discovery, so Gateway slot validation sees the same newly added source-root plugin that `plugins list` can see.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `src/plugins/plugin-registry-snapshot.ts`: Added `collectConfiguredPluginIds()` and `hasConfiguredGlobalSourcePluginMissingFromPersistedIndex()` functions; inserted check in the persisted-index staleness chain.\n- `src/plugins/plugin-registry-snapshot.test.ts`: Added regression test verifying configured source plugin is discovered when missing from stale persisted index.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Unit tests:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/plugin-registry-snapshot.test.ts` — 23/23 passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Test: configured source plugin missing from stale persisted registry**\n\n```\n// 1. Write a stale persisted index that does not contain memory-demo\n// 2. Add source-root plugin at state/extensions/memory-demo/openclaw.plugin.json\n// 3. Load registry — should detect the mismatch and fall back to derived\n\nresult.source === \"derived\"\n✓ diagnostics include \"persisted-registry-stale-source\"\n✓ memory-demo found with origin \"global\"\n```\n\n- ✅ Configured plugin missing from persisted index but present in extensions/ root → detected as stale, falls back to derived\n- ✅ Unchanged configs still use the fast persisted path\n- ✅ Only triggers when the plugin is actually referenced by config (not a blanket scan)\n\n**What was not tested:** Live `openclaw gateway` startup with a real third-party memory plugin (the regression covers the exact persisted-registry decision point used by Gateway config validation).\n\n- [x] AI-assisted",
        "branch": "fix/issue-96046-plugin-registry-scan-v2",
